					<head>Ḥidushim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Contains Novellae on the tractate Bava batra.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="260v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥidushim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חדושים</title>
							<note>
								<p>The authorship is uncertain, <ref target="Herschler_1965"/> attributes the work to Jonah ben Abraham Gerondi. The author quotes several rabbinic authorities, including Shemu᾿el ben Hofni, Asher ben Meshulam, Shelomoh ben Avraham of Montpellier or Maimonides.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/25683756">Jonah ben Abraham Gerondi, approximately 1200-1263</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/25683756">יונה בן אברהם, גרונדי</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>260 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>290</height>
